│ This happens when the VPlan cost model and the legacy cost model compute different optimal vectorization factors (VFs), and the VPlan for the VF chosen by the      │
│ VPlan model doesn't offer additional simplifications over the legacy choice.                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The reproducer involves a loop with a multiplicative reduction. The value multiplied in the reduction is derived from a `select` that depends on the induction      │
│ variable `%iv`:                                                                                                                                                     │
│ `%narrow.i = select i1 %cmp1.i, i32 1, i32 %iv` where `%cmp1.i` is true if `%iv` is even.                                                                           │
│ So, `%narrow.i` is 1 if `%iv` is even, and `%iv` if `%iv` is odd.                                                                                                   │
│ This value is then `zext`ed to `i64` and used in the reduction: `%red.next = mul nsw i64 %red, %mul`.                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The loop runs for `%iv = 0`. The exit condition is `icmp eq i32 %iv, 1`.                                                                                            │
│ - When `%iv = 0`: `%narrow.i` is 1, `%mul` is 1. `%red.next` becomes `12 * 1 = 12`. `%iv.next` is 1. The loop exits. The result is 12.                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The problem seems to be related to how Scalar Evolution (SCEV) analyzes the expression for `%mul`.                                                                  │
│ The expression is `zext(select(is_even(%iv)), 1, %iv))`.                                                                                                            │
│ SCEV can analyze this through `SCEVAddRecExpr`. The step recurrence for this expression is complex.                                                                 │
│ It seems the legacy cost model might be able to determine that for `%iv=0`, the value is 1, and since the loop only executes once, it can simplify the cost         │
│ calculation. The VPlan-based model might be failing to do so, leading to a different cost estimation and a different optimal VF.                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ A similar issue was reported in LLVM bug #56091, where a disagreement between cost models was caused by SCEV being able to simplify an expression that the VPlan    │
│ builder could not. The fix was to disable VPlan-native path if such a "SCEV-simplified" instruction is present in the loop.                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ The relevant code is in `LoopVectorizationPlanner::buildVPlans`.                                                                                                    │
│ ```cpp                                                                                                                                                              │
